BlueCP is a project which is still
in development and as such the code
in here is probably crap.

================================
General Notes Because I Forget:
================================
Create instance of Database to work with
$database = new Database('localhost', 'mydatabase', 'root', '123456');

Get all entries of a table
$allUsers = $database->select('example');

Example advanced query for searching
$usersBeginningWithLetterA = $database->select('example', '*', 'username LIKE \'%A%\'');

Insert new user to table user and get ID of row inserted
$userData = array(
    'username' => 'Max',
    'password' => 'as7d89',
); // Yes this is bad, its just an example

$userId = $database->insert('accounts', $userData);
echo $userId;

Update, e.g. to change users password
$database->update('accounts', array('password' => 'as7d999'), 'username = \'Max\'');

Delete user
$database->delete('user', $userId);

Truncate table (delete all rows in table and set index back)
$database->truncate('cache');